    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-04-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-04-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="177"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d177">
                <head>No. 52.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">West</persName> to Earl <persName
                            type="to">Granville</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-04-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 11, 1882</date>. (Received April
                        24.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: With reference to my dispatch of the 28th
                    ultimo, I have the honor to inclose herewith to your lordship copy of a further
                    note which I have received from the Secretary of State respecting the
                    imprisonment of William Lane.</p>
                <pb facs="0337" n="265" xml:id="pg_265"/>
                <p>From the correspondence inclosed in your lordship’s dispatch of the 29th ultimo,
                    it would seem that Mr. Frelinghuysen, in his communications with Mr. Lowell,
                    sought to connect this case with the question of the release of the
                    Irish-American suspects, as I anticipated he might do, as reported to your
                    lordship in my above-mentioned dispatch.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>L. S. SACKVILLE WEST.</signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No. 52.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">West</persName>
                        </hi>.</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State, Washington</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-04-10">
                                <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 10, 1882</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my reply of the 28th ultimo to
                        your note of the 24th of that month, in relation to the imprisonment of a
                        British subject named William Lane, at Detroit, Mich., I now have the honor
                        to inform you that I have received a letter from the attorney-general of
                        Michigan, in which that officer states that the prisoner in question has
                        been convicted of an assault with intent to murder,</p>
                    <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>F. T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
